cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AI 

This paper deals with estimating and tracking the available bandwidth on multiple paths in a network, which is a problem in network engineering and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses Bayesian inference and particle filters, which are common techniques in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the security implications of the proposed method, which could place it in the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a dynamic model and tracking algorithm, which could be seen as a control problem and place it in the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
